'''Arnu Fourie''' (born 23 April 1985) is a [[South African]] [[Paralympian]] [[Track and field|athlete]] who runs in the T44 class. His is a single-below-the-knee amputee.

==Life and career==
Fourie was born in [[Bloem]], and lost his left leg below the knee in a boating accident in 2003. He was playing rugby at the time, and took up running. He participated in the [[2008 Paralympic Games]] in Beijing, taking 4th place and 6th place in the 200 m final. He won a gold medal in the [[IAAF]] Golden League Meet in Paris.<ref>{{citation |url=http://www.icexpress.co.za/arnu_fourie.html|title=Arnu Fourie|accessdate=5 September 2012}}</ref>

Fourie won a gold medal at the 2012 Summer Paralympic Games in London on September 5, 2012, running the third leg as part of the South African 4x100m relay team. The team set a world record time of 41.78 seconds.<ref name="Relay">{{citation |url=http://www.supersport.com/paralympics/south-africa/news/120905/Gold_for_mens_relay_team_in_world_record_time|title=Gold for men's relay team in world record time|date=5 September 2012|accessdate=5 September 2012}}</ref> He also set a world record in the heats of the 200 m event with a time of 22.57s.

